STATE EX REL. ALI
v.
CLEVELAND 2016-1131 Supreme Court of Ohio. May 8, 2018

CASE ANNOUNCEMENTS

MOTION AND PROCEDURAL RULINGS

In Mandamus. Pursuant to R.C. 2710.06(B)(1), the court has been notified that the parties in this case have reached a settlement. The case is returned to the regular docket under S.Ct.Prac.R. 19.01. Within 60 days, the relator shall file either an application for dismissal or a notice of failure of settlement. This case will be dismissed for want of prosecution if an application for dismissal or a notice of failure of settlement is not filed within 60 days.
